WEBVTT

00:06.200 --> 00:08.451
♪

00:16.193 --> 00:17.169
I love driving back.

00:17.170 --> 00:19.423
I looked for a place down here
when I got my gold shield.

00:19.448 --> 00:20.651
So, what happened?

00:20.652 --> 00:22.385
Well, one month's rent
on a one-bedroom

00:22.387 --> 00:23.970
costs more than my car.

00:23.972 --> 00:26.556
Yeah. What's wrong
with Brooklyn anyway?

00:26.558 --> 00:28.925
Nothing, but, I mean,
check this out--

00:28.927 --> 00:30.677
it's beautiful,
it's safe.

00:30.679 --> 00:32.795
Well, judging
by the call we just got,

00:32.797 --> 00:34.981
I don't think
it's that safe.

00:34.983 --> 00:36.866
What do we got?

00:36.868 --> 00:38.451
Ted Kramer,
Wall Street guy.

00:38.453 --> 00:40.286
Gunshot to
the head.

00:43.440 --> 00:44.541
Close range.

00:44.543 --> 00:46.793
They didn't take
his fancy watch.

00:46.795 --> 00:48.294
No signs of forced entry?

00:48.296 --> 00:49.796
No, Detective.

00:49.798 --> 00:51.631
It's a serious security system.

00:51.633 --> 00:54.317
Checked it. Disabled.
Whoever pulled the trigger

00:54.319 --> 00:57.370
probably took care of that
after this guy let him in.

00:57.372 --> 00:59.872
No signs of a struggle,
nothing stolen.

00:59.874 --> 01:01.391
I don't think it's a burglary.

01:01.393 --> 01:02.926
Looks like a professional hit.

01:02.928 --> 01:06.479
Question is, who'd want. Kr?

01:07.431 --> 01:09.215
<i>Don't take this</i>

01:09.217 --> 01:10.350
the wrong way.

01:10.352 --> 01:12.318
You drive just like
my grandmother.

01:12.320 --> 01:15.572
Yeah, well, you drive like my
brother when he was 14, so...

01:15.574 --> 01:17.991
You can't drive
till you're 16, chief.

01:17.993 --> 01:18.588
Exactly.

01:18.613 --> 01:20.854
I'm just saying, it's not like
you're gonna get a ticket.

01:21.112 --> 01:23.913
Well, if I do, it's not like my
rich dad is gonna pay it for me.

01:23.915 --> 01:26.065
Boy Scout.
Daddy's girl.

01:26.067 --> 01:29.202
All units, shots fired,
corner of Clinton and 12th.

01:29.204 --> 01:30.837
12 David responding.

01:33.592 --> 01:35.425
That's more like it, yeah.

01:37.000 --> 01:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:49.773 --> 01:52.025
We got two suspects drawing
shots from behind that car.

01:52.027 --> 01:53.610
Okay.

01:55.029 --> 01:57.380
Go, go, go!

01:58.115 --> 01:59.765
Police! Drop your weapons!

02:02.903 --> 02:04.037
All right, stay here.
I'm going around.

02:04.039 --> 02:05.771
No.
Stay, stay.

02:08.525 --> 02:09.908
Give it up!

02:15.532 --> 02:17.783
You're not getting out of here!

02:22.756 --> 02:23.940
Drop your weapon!

02:23.965 --> 02:25.809
Drop it! Put 'em on the ground
right now! On the ground!

02:25.810 --> 02:27.927
On the ground! Put 'em down!
On the ground now!

02:27.929 --> 02:30.430
On the ground!
Hands behind your head!

02:30.432 --> 02:32.348
On the ground!

02:32.350 --> 02:34.600
Central, 12 David.
Keep 'em coming.

02:34.602 --> 02:35.768
I got two under.

02:35.770 --> 02:36.769
One fled the scene.

02:39.973 --> 02:41.741
Stay here.

02:48.182 --> 02:51.234
Why'd you have to shoot him?
The kid was unarmed.

02:52.887 --> 02:55.621
Hey. Hey, what happened?

02:55.623 --> 02:57.173
He had a gun.
I had no choice.

02:57.175 --> 03:01.094
That cop shot him in the back!
He didn't have a gun!

03:01.096 --> 03:03.012
He's just a damn kid!

03:03.014 --> 03:05.264
Central, 12 David.
I need a bus forthwith

03:05.266 --> 03:07.350
at 3275 Clinton,

03:07.352 --> 03:08.501
regarding one male shot.

03:08.503 --> 03:11.020
Oh. Where's the gun?
What happened?

03:11.022 --> 03:12.388
Uh, I don't know.
Calm down.

03:12.390 --> 03:14.273
I've been trying to
stop the bleeding.

03:16.611 --> 03:17.777
He didn't have
no damn gun!

03:17.779 --> 03:19.529
You shot him
for no reason!

03:19.531 --> 03:21.564
All right, all right,
hey, calm down. All right.

03:21.566 --> 03:24.033
All right, back up!
Central, 12 David.

03:24.035 --> 03:26.119
I'm requesting a 10-85,

03:26.121 --> 03:29.872
regarding large disorderly crowd
at this location, forthwith.

03:29.874 --> 03:31.690
All right, calm down!
Hey, back up!

03:31.692 --> 03:34.026
Back up!
Hey, back up!

03:34.028 --> 03:36.195
The current unrest
on Clinton Street began

03:36.197 --> 03:40.083
when 14-year-old Marcus Green,
fleeing purported gang members,

03:40.085 --> 03:42.251
was chased by NYPD officer
James Montero,

03:42.253 --> 03:44.554
who then shot the youth
in the back.

03:44.556 --> 03:47.056
There's no word on the boy's
condition at this time.

03:47.058 --> 03:49.042
So far, police
haven't engaged protestors,

03:49.044 --> 03:52.678
but violence
is clearly escalating.

03:54.015 --> 03:56.566
Kid died on the table
five minutes ago.

03:56.568 --> 03:58.217
Five minutes from now,

03:58.219 --> 03:59.652
the news will hit the street.

03:59.654 --> 04:01.053
Like a bombshell.

04:01.055 --> 04:02.355
We're ready.
How?

04:02.357 --> 04:03.906
Sheer numbers,
for starters.

04:03.908 --> 04:06.526
Contain the crowd without
inciting further violence.

04:06.528 --> 04:08.077
It's easier said than done.

04:08.079 --> 04:10.947
They are to stand down
unless directly attacked.

04:10.949 --> 04:12.749
What about attacks
on private property?

04:12.751 --> 04:14.951
I will not have someone shot
over a plateglass window.

04:14.953 --> 04:16.753
What are they saying?

04:16.755 --> 04:18.087
Witnesses claim
that Green was unarmed,

04:18.089 --> 04:21.673
including local shop owner
Marta Dominga.

04:21.676 --> 04:23.543
Marta, please. Thank you.
Thank you for talking to us.

04:23.545 --> 04:25.762
Can you please tell us what
happened and what were your thoughts.

04:25.764 --> 04:27.547
Well, the cops come
into this neighborhood

04:27.549 --> 04:29.788
and they treat everyone
like a damn criminal,

04:29.813 --> 04:30.717
and we're sick of it!

04:30.718 --> 04:32.885
This is not right at all,
because this boy

04:32.887 --> 04:34.687
was 14 years old.

04:34.689 --> 04:36.189
Did he have a gun?

04:36.191 --> 04:38.141
No, he had not gun.
And that's not right.

04:38.143 --> 04:40.810
I mean, what about us?
What about <i>our</i> neighborhood?

04:40.812 --> 04:43.062
We need some protection, too...

04:43.064 --> 04:44.814
They find the weapon yet?

04:44.816 --> 04:47.900
Not yet. All due respect, boss,
we can't put that fire out

04:47.902 --> 04:49.202
with just a squirt gun.

04:49.204 --> 04:50.987
Do we have trained officers
on the scene?

04:50.989 --> 04:51.937
Yes.
Then let's put

04:51.939 --> 04:53.322
that training
to good use.

04:53.324 --> 04:55.458
We will play for a tie
until further notice.

04:55.460 --> 04:57.126
Yes, sir.
I am late

04:57.128 --> 04:59.212
for my briefing with the mayor.
Sir, Montero's

04:59.214 --> 05:01.547
a good officer--
no need to play defense here.

05:01.549 --> 05:05.784
We got a 14-year-old boy
shot dead by one of our own.

05:05.786 --> 05:08.421
The reality is, public sentiment
is going to dictate

05:08.423 --> 05:10.223
how some of this goes.

05:10.225 --> 05:12.308
Just trying to stand up
for our guy.

05:12.310 --> 05:14.427
I'll stand up for him.

05:14.429 --> 05:17.480
Let's just hope
he did the right thing.

